pomointer - pomofile interpreter
================================
pomointer is the only pomofile interpreter in the world.

A pomofile is a text file containing information about
how many pomodoros you spent doing a task. 
See examples/ directory for examples, also check
pomofile(5) man page.

If you want to see a example in action run
    
    make
    make run_all


Requirements
------------
A Linux distro.


Installation
------------
Edit Makefile to match your local setup. pomointer is 
by default installed at /usr/local namespace.

Then, enter the following command to build and install
(if necessary as root).

      make clean install


Running pomointer
-----------------
See pomointer(1) man page for usage information or run

      pomointer -h


